{"lemma": "مُثَنّاةٌ", "slug": "مُثَنّاةٌ", "root": "ث.ن.#", "root_slug": "ث-ن-_", "root_link": "/words/roots/ث-ن-_", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "مُثَنَّى", "root": "ثني", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 3}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["adj"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n4784", "n4785"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%A9%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "folded book", "fa": "کتاب دوتایی", "ur": "دوہی کا کتاب", "tr": "katlanmış kitap", "id": "buku lipat", "bn": "ভাঁজ করা বই", "es": "libro doblado", "fr": "livre plié", "de": "gefaltetes Buch", "ru": "сложенная книга", "zh": "折叠的书"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "bent, folded, kinked, flexed"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the passive participle of ثَنَى (ṯanā, “to bend”)."}, "ipa": ["/maθ.nijj/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n4784", "headword_ar": "مَثْنَاةٌ", "root": "vnY", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "; pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavaAnK", "text_ar": "مَثَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vinoYN", "text_ar": "ثِنْىٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vinaAyapN", "text_ar": "ثِنَايَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavonFY", "text_ar": "مَثْنًى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; the last in two places. ―         -b2-  It is said in a trad. that one of the signs of the resurrection will be the public reading, or reciting, of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavonaAp", "text_ar": "مَثْنَاة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, S,) which means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "That which has been desired to be transcribed from a source other than the Book of God:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a certain book,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, K,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the Mishna,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which the learned men, and the recluses, of the Children of Israel, after Moses, composed after their own desire, from a source other than the Book of God,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as A'Obeyd says on the authority of a man learned in the books of the earlier times, (T,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "containing the histories of the Children of Israel after Moses, in which they allowed and disallowed what they pleased:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what is sung:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what is called in Persian"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "duw bayotiY", "text_ar": "دُو بَيْتِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which means two verses, each composed of a pair of hemistichs;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;) i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what is sung;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but A'Obeyd explains it otherwise than thus: (S:) it is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what is known among the 'Ajam by the term"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavonawiY~N", "text_ar": "مَثْنَوِىٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as though this were a rel. n. from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavonaApN", "text_ar": "مَثْنَاةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the vulgar say [erroneously]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*uw bayot", "text_ar": "ذُو بَيْت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with the pointed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*", "text_ar": "ذ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.)"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 361}], "source_refs": ["T", "S", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n4785", "headword_ar": "مِثْنَاةٌ", "root": "vnY", "bod